"n.(在金银上的)纯度印记；特征 【英】 n. 特征(distinctive feature) 【考】 反义词：uncharacter istic feature(无特点的标 志) 【例】 Attention to detail ishte hallmark of a fire craftsman. n. (金银的)纯度标记; (显而易见的)特征 【记】mark(n 标志; 分数; 记号) 【反】uncharacteristic feature(无特点的标志) 【记】源自伦敦金匠厅的标记，mark from Goldsmiths' Hall,出自那的金子有个mark→hallmark；音：好 + mark 印着好mark的金子意味着纯度好 hallmark (n.)  1721, official stamp of purity in gold and silver articles, from Goldsmiths' Hall in London, site of the assay office; see hall + mark (n.1). General sense of ""mark of quality"" first recorded 1864. As a verb from 1773."
